value.def: A turtle is a large reptile which has a thick shell covering its body and which lives in the sea most of the time.

value.boxr_value: in AM, use 美国英语用 sea turtle

value.def: A turtle is any reptile that has a thick shell around its body, for example a tortoise or terrapin.
If a boat turns turtle, it turns upside down when it is in the water.

example.ex: The tug nearly turned turtle twice, but I managed to keep her upright.
example.tran: 拖船两次都差点翻个儿，但我设法稳住了船身。
